[*]
xpl_email_sntx: [ref]: IETF RFC1034 (p.9), RFC1912 (p.3)\nEmail addresses are converted by using the following rule:\n   <local-part>@<mail-domain>  ==>  <local-part>.<mail-domain>\nif <local-part> contains a dot in should be backslashed (for 'bind')

[chk_soa]
testname: SOA record present
error   : No SOA record found on server
ok	: SOA record found
explain : [none]


[chk_soa_auth]
testname: SOA authoritative answer
error   : The SOA answer is not authoritative
ok	: The SOA answer is authoritative
explain : [none]


[chk_soa_contact_sntx_at]
testname: missused '@' characters in SOA contact name
error   : The contact name contains the character '@'
ok	: No missuse of '@' character in SOA contact name
explain = xpl_email_sntx


[chk_soa_contact_sntx]
testname: illegal characters in SOA contact name
error   : The contact name contains illegal characters
ok	: No illegal characters in SOA contact name
explain = xpl_email_sntx


[chk_soa_master_sntx]
testname: illegal characters in SOA master nameserver
error   : The SOA master nameserver contains illegal characters
ok	: No illegal characters in SOA master nameserver
explain = label_xpl


[chk_soa_master_fq]
testname: fully qualified master nameserver in SOA
error   : The SOA master nameserver is not fully qualified
ok	: The SOA master nameserver is fully qualified
explain : [none]
details : The master nameserver (%{mname}) is certainly missing the final dot in the configuration file.


[chk_soa_serial_fmt_YYYYMMDDnn]
testname: serial number of the form YYYYMMDDnn
error   : The format of the serial number is not YYYYMMDDnn
ok	: The serial numbre follow the form YYYYMMDDnn
explain : [ref]: RFC1912 (p.3)\nThe recommended syntax is YYYYMMDDnn (YYYY=year, MM=month, DD=day,\nnn=revision number).
details : The serial %{serial} doesn't seem to be in the YYYYMMDDnn format.


[chk_soa_refresh_6h]
testname: SOA 'refresh' at least 6 hours
error   : The 'refresh' period should be at least 6 hours
ok	: The 'refresh' is at least 6 hours
explain : [ref]: RFC1912 (p.3) and RIPE-203
details : The refresh (%{refresh} sec) should be at least 6 hours (21600 sec), you should correct this value.


[chk_soa_retry_refresh]
testname: SOA 'retry' lower than 'refresh'
error   : The 'retry' period must be lower than the 'refresh' period
ok	: The 'retry' is lower than the 'refresh'
explain : [ref]: IETF RFC1912 (p.4)\nThe 'retry' value is typically a fraction of the 'refresh' interval.
details : The retry (%{retry} sec) should be lower than the refresh (%{refresh} sec), you should correct one of these values.


[chk_soa_retry_1h]
testname: SOA 'retry' at least 1 hour
error   : The 'retry' period should be at least 1 hour
ok	: The 'retry' is at least 1 hour
explain : [ref]: RFC1912 (p.3) and RIPE-203
details : The retry (%{retry} sec) should be at least 1 hour (3600 sec), you should correct this value.


[chk_soa_expire_7d]
testname: SOA 'expire' at least 7 days
error   : The 'expire' period must be at least 7 days
ok	: The 'expire' is at least 7 days
explain : [ref]: IETF RFC1912 (p.4)\nAfter a zone is expired a secondary will still continue to try to contact\nthe primary, but it will no longer provide nameservice for the zone.\n2 to 4 weeks are suggested values.\n[ref]: AFNIC constraint\nA minimum of 1 week (7 days) is enforced.
details : The expire (%{expire} sec) should be at least 7 days (604800 sec), you should correct this value.


[chk_soa_expire_7refresh]
testname: SOA 'expire' at least 7 times 'refresh'
error   : The 'expire' period must be at least 7 times greater than 'refresh'
ok	: The 'expire' is at least 7 times the 'refresh'
explain : [none]
details : The expire (%{expire} sec) is not at least 7 times greater than the refresh (%{refresh} sec), you should correct one of them.


[chk_soa_minimum_1d]
testname: SOA 'minimum' less than 1 day
error   : The 'minimum' period should be less than 1 day
ok	: The 'minimum' is less than 1 day
explain : [ref]: RFC2308 (p.9) 5. Caching Negative Answers\nValues of one to three hours have been found to work well\nand would make sensible a default.  Values exceeding one day have\nbeen found to be problematic.
details : The minimum value is %{minimum} sec, and should be less than 1 day (86400 sec), the recommanded value is between 1 and 3 hours.


[chk_soa_ns_cname]
testname: SOA master is not an alias
error   : SOA master is not allowed to point to a CNAME alias
ok	: The SOA master is not an alias
explain = ns_cname_xpl
details : The master (%{master}) is a CNAME alias to %{alias}.


[chk_soa_vs_any]
testname: coherence between SOA and ANY records
error   : SOA and ANY request disagree
ok	: SOA and ANY agree
explain : [none]


[chk_soa_coherence_serial]
testname: coherence of serial number with primary nameserver
error   : The serial number is not coherent with primary nameserver
ok	: The serial number is coherent with primary nameserver
explain : [none]
details : got serial %{serial_this} instead of %{serial_ref} as on %{host_ref}.


[chk_soa_coherence_contact]
testname: coherence of administrative contact with primary nameserver
error   : The contact is not coherent with primary nameserver
ok	: The contact is coherent with primary nameserver
explain : [none]
details : got contact %{rname_this} instead of %{rname_ref} as on %{host_ref}.


[chk_soa_coherence_master]
testname: coherence of master with primary nameserver
error   : The master is not coherent with primary nameserver
ok	: The master is coherent with primary nameserver
explain : [none]
details : got master %{mname_this} instead of %{mname_ref} as on %{host_ref}.

[chk_soa_coherence]
testname: coherence of SOA with primary nameserver
error   : The SAO is not coherent with primary nameserver
ok	: The SOA is coherent with primary nameserver
explain : [none]

